 After shocking South Africa by implementing unprecedented Stage 6 load shedding on Monday night, Eskom said that it has since recovered some of its generating power and will implement Stage 4 load shedding throughout the day on Tuesday. "Eskom unreservedly apologises to South Africans as Stage 6 rotational loadshedding shifts back to Stage 4 from 22:00 today until 23:00 on Tuesday," the utility said.   #POWERALERT 4Date: 09 December 2019Eskom unreservedly apologises to South Africans as Stage 6 rotational loadshedding shifts back to Stage 4 from 22:00 today until 23:00 on Tuesday.@News24 @TimesLIVE @eNCA @iol @SABCNewsOnline @TheCitizen_News @SAfmRadio @POWER987News pic.twitter.com/H2YOxOrHLH  Rotational load shedding is expected to continue at least for the rest of this week. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.   